,Recommended,247240,34227122,Posted: 13 August,all,DarkKingBowser,"I've seen a lot of people complaining that the game is way too hard or unfair or controls badly, which is complete ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥t. I don't play Ghost 'n Goblins because it's easy, I don't play Spelunky because I enjoy not advancing. I play them for the challenge and for the feeling of accomplishment after every level I beat.Volgarr the Viking requires more skill than luck. In the first world there is a checkpoint at the beginning of the world and a checkpoint in the next room of the world; that's it. You must study enemies, know how many hits they can take, how to dodge them, and when to attack. Once you understand these things the levels become easier and easier. Every death is a learning expereince, every single foot into the unknown gives you more knowledge for your next attempt. Chests give you upgrades that help you kill enemies but dissapear once you get hit. Get all the upgrades and any enemy in your way will be obliterated.I recommend this game highly, especially for a low price. If you like Ghost 'n Goblins, Rogue Legacy, Crypt of the Necrodancer, Castlevania, Spelunky, etc. you are going to love this game.Now if you'll excuse me, I've got some fish to spear."
