,Recommended,247240,7971085,"Posted: 8 December, 2013",all,Emerald Witch,"Be the viking... Or die trying, a lot! Having actually finished this game I feel qualified to recommend it to anyone who likes extremely difficult platformers. Volgarr is something of an anomaly, a game that could have been made back in 1990, but works so very well today. It is not the same kind of fast paced action featured in games like Super Meat Boy, though. It is slower, more deliberate, and much more violent. Every movement must be deliberate and you will die a lot just figuring out when to jump, what the boss pattern is, etc... However, you do get unlimited lives and the most you have to backtrack is maybe 5-7 minutes after dying to a boss, if that. If this doesn't sound like fun to you, it might not be, but it feels great once you've mastered the levels and bosses, eventually being able to clear them without even getting hit once. Oh, and you do get armor pickups that enhance your abilities and you can take 2-3 hits before dying depending on your items, and can block most ranged attacks. The game is very fair, just very hard.There is a lot more to the game than most people will ever see, as well. By completing levels perfectly (or near perfectly) you gain ""lives"" you can use in extra-challenging alternate levels. There are 4 or 5 of these, and when you run out of lives in them you get dropped back into the main game levels, at which point you can try to win them without getting hurt again and get back into the alternates. There are 3 different endings based on how many of these you complete.I'll wrap up with a quick tip for anyone who buys the game and wants to actually finish it... Press left on the title screen to warp to the next level. You can keep doing  this all the way to the end game tower assuming you actually beat the boss of the level you're skipping over."
