,Recommended,247240,34195235,Posted: 12 August,all,JackieUnfinished,"Okay, this game is good. Really good, in fact.Is it hard as balls? Yes.Does it rely on trial and error? Sometimes, yeah.Is it unfair? No, not really.The controls are perfectly fine. Not being able to change the trajectory of your jump in midair is a deliberate decision and it integrates perfectly with the game's philosophy. You can't go jumping around recklessly becasue you'll get killed, but that's kinda the point. Attacking and rolling work exactly as intended and very rarely do your inputs not translate the way you expect on screen.Level and enemy design are actually pretty clever. Almost every action and power-up is useful in more than one way and the levels make use of it, Enemies are, on the other hand, are spread in a way that create very different situations. There are some areas where weaker enemies respawn and force you to be quick and precise, while others encourage you to be cautious and methodical, having to remember the way a particular enemy moves and being on the lookout for potential traps. Both enemies and level structure seem to vastly differ from level to level, so you'll need to approach each of them with a new strategy.So, yeah, if you like classic sidescroller action platformers in the vein of Castlevania or Ghost 'n' Goblins you'll love this game, and even if you don't I think it still deserves a chance, because it's a damn fun game."
