,Recommended,247240,10226177,"Posted: 24 May, 2014",all,Porthos,"Great game, but incredibly difficult and reminiscent of older games like Ghost 'n Goblins. If you love those old games, you'll love this. This is a game that is almost entirely skill-based. If you want a game that will hold your hand you aren't going to get it here. Every enemy you encounter has a specific way of being defeated that will often require you to have a solid grasp of the fighting and platforming mechanics.There's a limited save system that allows you to resume roughtly where you left off, but you'll need to collect lives in-game--and likely play the game in one-sitting--to beat the optional later levels and get the best ending. That might seem a bit too harsh, but once you get the core gameplay down you'll be able to get to the final boss in about an hour.In short: Difficult, but extremely fun, and with good core gameplay that's difficult without feeling cheap."
