76561198098830441,Recommended,247240,8014544,"Posted: 12 December, 2013",all,Volket,"Do you want to play a hardcore Action/Platformer? Do you want to face hordes of monsters simply to prove yourself a badass? Do you want to be a man? If the answer to all these are yes I cannot recommend this game enough. This is a throwback to everything good about the ""good old days"" where games were made to challenge you to the maximum. This game is challenging with great focus on detail of the system.Volgarr the Viking is an amazing game created by Crazy Viking Studios which pushes the players to their potential. You play as the games namesake Volgarr on a quest to be a badass. This game has a great soundtrack that keeps you tense and feeling like the Viking you are. Controls are responsive and tight leaving you feeling that any death is your own mistake.  Visually this game looks great for being a throwback to the days of the arcade, which in my humble opinion is a plus, having wonderful 2d sprites which bring the game to gory life.This game has good ability to be played again and again, which you'll likely be doing because each time you die you must go back to your last checkpoint, which can be quite a loss of progress. I'm not kidding this game is truly hard, and it will challenge you. Its simplistic controls leave the only challenge you face be the hordes of enemies who will stop at nothing to kill Volgarr and end his quest, which will likely happen more than you want it to. Luckily for our hero death is not the end for him, for each time he dies he returns to life at his last check point. Check points are a rare occurrence though, keeping you on your toes for fear of losing your progress so far.Power ups appear in the form of armor which grants you extra health, each time you are hit however you lose that piece of equipment and ability it brought with it. The only downside is the lack of any form of storytelling, and the lack of saving which can make the challenge all the 