,Recommended,247240,9666725,"Posted: 29 March, 2014",all,Thy Dungeonman,"Volgarr is a throwback to certain challenging 16-bit platformers, namely Super Ghouls 'N Ghosts and Rastan. The graphics are a little odd- they look kind of like a SNES game with the ""filtering"" turned on to make the pixels look smoothed, but I actually do like them. More importantly, the mechanics are top notch. With these kind of games, controls and mechanics absolutely make or break the game. Volgarr has Rastan style swordplay (attack while moving, block with shield, etc) and Ghouls 'N Ghosts style platforming (a nice, crisp-feeling double jump) and powerups (chests upgrade your shield/armor/weapon depending on what you've got currently, allowing you to use new moves and take more hits).Volgarr has a sword and a spear, and that's it. The game really makes it work, giving you a range of options. You can fight while moving, play defensive and trade blows with your shield, dodge roll, jump attack, downstab, throw spears, charge spear attack, throw spears in midair, throw spears into walls to make new platforms, and so on. All of this is highly intuitive and you'll find yourself doing some really cool maneuvers very naturally. I kind of amazed myself just now when I jumped into an area, threw a spear in midair to kill a wasp, downstabbed to kill a lizardman, dodge rolled past an arrow trap, and then jumped onto a spear I threw earlier to climb out of the pit before another arrow could fire.It's important to know that Volgarr is very oldschool. That means no saving. Every time you launch the game, there isn't even a start menu, Volgarr is borne out of blood and bone and you start killing lizardmen immediately. You begin from level 1 every time you launch the game. You do have infinite lives, but checkpoints aren't highly frequent, and you'll need to beat the game in one sitting. I believe that beating a level without dying takes you down an alternate path for the next level, and beating the entire game without dying gives you a secret ending.My only complaint is that I wish that the game had better music. It deserves more metal music!"
