76561198132348862,Recommended,247240,31382357,Posted: 26 April,all,Logi,"Rise, Warrior!ROAR!Volgarr the Viking is an awesome game. It has great graphics, excellent gameplay and a great soundtrack.There will be minor spoilers for the story:You play Volgarr, a viking with a mighty sword and an unlimited supply of spears that he can use to attack enemies or use as platforms. Your task is to travel through five worlds (each consisting of two sections) and defeat the bosses to open Fafnir's tower.Should you be good enough, you can obtain warrior spirits that serve as lives to play the more difficult parts of worlds 2-6.Depending on what you do, you can earn one out of three endings.Mark my words though: This game is not for everybody. It has a high difficulty spike.Playing Volgarr for the first time can be extremely frustrating. I spent 3 hours of my first playthrough in the first two worlds before I got good enough alone. However the more I learned how to control Volgarr and the neat tricks he can do, the easier it got. Now I got all achievements and just completed the game a second time on the Valkyrie path.I would say that Volgarr is basically Dark Souls the Jump n' Run. Once you have learned the game's tricks, it becomes extremely enjoyable and rewarding.Try to answer these questions:Do you like to get challenged by a game?Do you like to try, try, try again until you finally beat a world?Do you like to eventually master a hard game and feel like a beast when you played through it a second, third or even fourth and so forth time?If you can answer all these questions with yes, then you should check out Volgarr.If you don't like to get constantly killed until you finally mastered a difficult section, then better turn around now and look for something else to play."
