,Recommended,247240,10265561,"Posted: 28 May, 2014",all,Atticus Zed,"Many games these days attest to having ""NES hard"" difficulty, but only a few truly understand what that means. Volgarr the Viking is one of those precious gems. It finds its difficulty, not in cheap deaths or overpowered enemies, but by giving you a variety of ways to deal with challenges and leaving it up to you to decide which course of action will lead to success, and leaving it in your hands to execute it flawlessly.Every step towards the end introduces a new challenge, combining existing traps and enemies in a new way, forcing you to rethink your new strategy on the fly or die trying. It is not unfair, however, and introduces any new traps or enemies well in advance on their own, before blending them with any other traps or foes.The secrets are superb, especially Thor's blessing, which (as far as I've seen) requires the unwavering courage to climb down to the very edge of a vine to strike at a hidden wall, or down-thrust your sword into a flower that spews deadly spores straight into your face.This game is certainly no slouch. It will break you, but if you have the strength to persevere, you will rise from your own ashes and pay this game back every blow it has dealt you."
