,Recommended,247240,18940456,"Posted: 7 November, 2015",all,rokku,"All right, comparing other games to Dark Souls possibly the most unoriginal thing I could possibly do, but I'm gonna do it anyway. Volgarr the Viking is pretty much the Dark Souls of 2D platformers. In a similar way, you need to think every enemy as a serious threat. Progress is slow and you must move carefully.Challenge is a nice thing, but I think this game is way too unforgiving. The most obvious thing is the lack of checkpoints. If you are defeated, it usually means you will go to the beginning of the level, and that may get super frustrating. And that happens easily, because the character can only take like 1-2 hits. I'm actually pretty okay with that, but I just don't like the lack of checkpoints. Have at least a few more, huh?The game itself is still pretty good. The jumping controls may take some time getting used to (think how it was in the first Castlevania games, as you can't move during your jump, but at least you have a double jump to once turn in the air). Graphics are nice, not the best there is, but still they do their job. Game itself works very smoothly.Still giving a thumbs up. Only recommended to those who are ready for challenge and trial-and-error gameplay. Difficult, but rewarding."
