,Recommended,247240,7380141,"Posted: 13 October, 2013",all,Final Contra,"This is a breath of fresh air from the modern era of games where the first 2 hours of a game are a tutorial, every enemy has a neon flashing weakpoint, and you're fully capable of hiding everytime you scrape your knee to regain your health. No, none of that♥♥♥♥♥♥with Völgarr the Viking. This is a throwback to the glory days when games didn't hold your hand. Instead Odin hands you a sword, shield, and spear and sends you on you way with a simple ""Rise, Warrior. Don't ♥♥♥♥ this up."" It's another shining example of how being difficult without resorting to low-blows always results in an extremely rewarding experience.My one word of caution is that you'll have to play the game in a single playthrough like the old days since there's no save system. With that being said, you could easily pause and leave the game running in the background when you need to take a break. As a gauge of what you're in for, it took me 3 hours 26 minutes and 94 deaths to finish my first playthrough and I'd say I'm good at these kind of games."
